==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cannel coal
<hw>Can"nel coal`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Corrupt. fr. <ets>candle
coal</ets>.]</ety> <def>A kind of mineral coal of a black color,
sufficiently hard and solid to be cut and polished. It burns readily,
with a clear, yellow flame, and on this account has been used as a
substitute for candles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cannele</ent>⟦br⟧
